## 12. Test Strategy
<!-- Last Updated: YYYY-MM-DD -->
<!-- What is tested, what tools are used, what constitutes pass/fail, and entry/exit criteria for
     Phase 3. This is the project's authoritative test plan. Add project-specific test types and
     tools in place of the bracketed placeholders. The SAST, dependency, secret detection, and
     license rows are mandatory for all projects. Update the Bug Severity and UAT tables to match
     project context.
     Format: Tables
     Source: Step 1.4 — Test Planning -->

| Test Type | Tool | What It Covers | Pass Criteria | Phase |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Unit | [framework] | Individual functions/methods | All pass, >80% coverage | 2 |
| Integration | [framework] | Component interactions | All pass | 2-3 |
| E2E | [framework] | Full user journeys | All pass | 3 |
| SAST | Semgrep | Static vulnerability analysis | Zero critical/high | 2-3 |
| Dependency | Snyk | Known vulnerabilities in dependencies | Zero critical/high | 2-3 |
| Secret Detection | gitleaks | Hardcoded secrets | Zero findings | 2-3 |
| License | [tool] | License compliance | No copyleft in dependencies | 2-3 |
| Accessibility | [tool] | WCAG AA compliance | Score >= target | 3 |
| Performance | [tool] | Startup, latency, memory | Within targets | 3 |

### Bug Severity Classification

| Severity | Definition | Examples | Can Defer? |
|---|---|---|---|
| **SEV-1** | Data loss, security breach, app crash on core flow | Auth bypass, database corruption, crash on login | No — must fix immediately |
| **SEV-2** | Feature broken but workaround exists, significant UX failure | Form submits wrong data, layout broken on one platform | Yes — must resolve or remove feature at Phase 2→3 gate |
| **SEV-3** | Minor UX issue, cosmetic, non-core edge case | Alignment off, tooltip truncated, rare edge case | Yes |
| **SEV-4** | Enhancement, suggestion, polish | "Would be nice if..." | Automatic Post-MVP |

### UAT Plan

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Testing interval | Every [N] features |
| Human tester count | [N] |
| Bug tracking tool | [tool or BUGS.md] |
| UAT format | Interactive HTML (tests/uat/templates/test-session-template.html) |

